{"question": "Which chemical is used for blood anticoagulation in CBC?", "answer": "EDTA (Ethylenediaminetetraacetic acid) is commonly used."},
{"question": "What is ESR test?", "answer": "ESR (Erythrocyte Sedimentation Rate) measures inflammation in the body."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in ESR test?", "answer": "EDTA or sodium citrate may be used depending on method."},
{"question": "What is blood glucose test?", "answer": "Blood glucose test measures the level of sugar in blood to diagnose diabetes."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in glucose test?", "answer": "Glucose oxidase or hexokinase reagents are commonly used."},
{"question": "What is lipid profile?", "answer": "A lipid profile measures cholesterol, triglycerides, HDL, and LDL levels in blood."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used to measure cholesterol?", "answer": "Enzymatic reagents such as cholesterol esterase and cholesterol oxidase."},
{"question": "What is liver function test (LFT)?", "answer": "LFT measures enzymes, proteins, and bilirubin to assess liver health."},
