{"question": "What is urinalysis?", "answer": "Urinalysis is the examination of urine for physical, chemical, and microscopic properties."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used to detect protein in urine?", "answer": "Sulphosalicylic acid or dipstick reagents."},
{"question": "What is microbiology culture?", "answer": "Microbiology culture is growing microorganisms in a suitable medium to identify pathogens."},
{"question": "Which media is used for bacterial culture?", "answer": "Nutrient agar, MacConkey agar, blood agar, etc."},
{"question": "What is Gram staining?", "answer": "Gram staining is a technique to differentiate bacteria into Gram-positive and Gram-negative."},
{"question": "Which chemicals are used in Gram staining?", "answer": "Crystal violet, iodine, alcohol (decolorizer), and safranin."},
{"question": "What is acid-fast staining?", "answer": "A staining technique used to detect Mycobacterium tuberculosis."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in acid-fast staining?", "answer": "Carbol fuchsin, acid-alcohol, and methylene blue."},
{"question": "What is histopathology?", "answer": "Histopathology studies tissues to detect disease under a microscope."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used for tissue fixation?", "answer": "Formalin (10% neutral buffered formalin) is commonly used."},
