{"question": "What is hematoxylin and eosin (H&E) stain?", "answer": "H&E staining is used to visualize tissue morphology under a microscope."},
{"question": "Which chemical is hematoxylin?", "answer": "Hematoxylin is a natural dye that stains nuclei blue-purple."},
{"question": "Which chemical is eosin?", "answer": "Eosin stains cytoplasm and extracellular matrix pink."},
{"question": "What is immunohistochemistry?", "answer": "A technique using antibodies to detect specific proteins in tissue sections."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in immunohistochemistry?", "answer": "Primary and secondary antibodies, chromogens like DAB."},
{"question": "What is cytology?", "answer": "Cytology studies individual cells to detect abnormalities or cancer."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used for cell fixation in cytology?", "answer": "Alcohol or formalin-based fixatives."},
{"question": "What is Pap smear?", "answer": "Pap smear screens for cervical cancer by examining cells from the cervix."},
{"question": "Which stain is used in Pap smear?", "answer": "Papanicolaou stain (hematoxylin, orange G, eosin azure)."},
{"question": "What is coagulation test?", "answer": "Coagulation tests evaluate blood clotting ability."},
{"question": "Which test measures PT?", "answer": "Prothrombin time (PT) test."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in PT test?", "answer": "Thromboplastin and calcium chloride."},
{"question": "What is aPTT test?", "answer": "Activated Partial Thromboplastin Time test measures intrinsic pathway of coagulation."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in aPTT?", "answer": "Phospholipid, calcium chloride, and activator."},
{"question": "What is blood grouping?", "answer": "Blood grouping determines the ABO and Rh type of blood."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in blood grouping?", "answer": "Anti-A, Anti-B, and Anti-D (for Rh) sera."},
{"question": "What is crossmatch?", "answer": "Crossmatch tests compatibility between donor and recipient blood before transfusion."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in crossmatch?", "answer": "Antisera and Coombs reagent."},
{"question": "What is urine culture?", "answer": "Urine culture grows bacteria from urine to identify infections."},
{"question": "Which media is used in urine culture?", "answer": "MacConkey agar and CLED agar."},
{"question": "What is stool examination?", "answer": "Stool examination checks for parasites, blood, and infection."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in stool ova and parasite test?", "answer": "Saline, iodine, and formalin for preservation."},
{"question": "What is ELISA test?", "answer": "ELISA detects antibodies or antigens in blood."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in ELISA?", "answer": "Antigens/antibodies coated on plate, enzyme-linked antibodies, and substrate like TMB."},
{"question": "What is PCR test?", "answer": "Polymerase Chain Reaction amplifies DNA to detect pathogens or genetic material."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in PCR?", "answer": "DNA polymerase, primers, nucleotides, and buffer."},
{"question": "What is serology?", "answer": "Serology studies antibodies and antigens in blood serum."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in serology?", "answer": "Antigens, antibodies, and reagents for agglutination or precipitation."},
{"question": "What is blood urea test?", "answer": "Measures urea in blood to assess kidney function."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in blood urea test?", "answer": "Urease and diacetyl monoxime reagents."},
{"question": "What is creatinine test?", "answer": "Measures creatinine levels to assess kidney function."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used for creatinine test?", "answer": "Alkaline picrate (Jaffe method)."},
{"question": "What is serum electrolytes test?", "answer": "Measures sodium, potassium, chloride, and bicarbonate levels in blood."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in sodium/potassium test?", "answer": "Ion-selective electrodes or flame photometry reagents."},
{"question": "What is uric acid test?", "answer": "Measures uric acid to check for gout or kidney disease."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in uric acid test?", "answer": "Uricase or phosphotungstic acid method."},
{"question": "What is serum calcium test?", "answer": "Measures calcium in blood to assess bone and parathyroid health."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in calcium test?", "answer": "O-cresolphthalein complexone (OCPC) method."},
{"question": "What is serum phosphate test?", "answer": "Measures inorganic phosphate in blood."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in phosphate test?", "answer": "Ammonium molybdate and acidic reagents."},
{"question": "What is liver enzyme AST?", "answer": "Aspartate transaminase (AST) indicates liver or muscle damage."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used to detect AST?", "answer": "2-oxoglutarate and NADH in enzymatic assay."},
{"question": "What is ALT test?", "answer": "Alanine transaminase (ALT) indicates liver damage."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used to detect ALT?", "answer": "L-alanine, 2-oxoglutarate, and NADH in enzymatic assay."},
{"question": "What is alkaline phosphatase (ALP) test?", "answer": "ALP test measures enzyme related to liver and bone disease."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in ALP test?", "answer": "p-nitrophenyl phosphate substrate in alkaline medium."},
{"question": "What is bilirubin test?", "answer": "Measures bilirubin in blood to assess liver function."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in bilirubin test?", "answer": "Diazo reagent in Jendrassik-Grof method."},
{"question": "What is amylase test?", "answer": "Measures pancreatic enzyme amylase to assess pancreatic function."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in amylase test?", "answer": "Starch substrate and iodine or enzymatic assay reagents."},
{"question": "What is lipase test?", "answer": "Measures pancreatic enzyme lipase for pancreatic function assessment."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in lipase test?", "answer": "Triglyceride substrates or synthetic esters."},
{"question": "What is CRP test?", "answer": "C-reactive protein test measures inflammation levels in the body."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in CRP test?", "answer": "Antibodies against CRP in immunoassays."},
{"question": "What is HbA1c test?", "answer": "HbA1c measures average blood glucose over 2-3 months."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in HbA1c test?", "answer": "Chromatography or immunoassay reagents."},
{"question": "What is serum protein electrophoresis?", "answer": "Separates and measures different proteins in blood."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in serum protein electrophoresis?", "answer": "Buffer solutions and stains like Coomassie blue."},
{"question": "What is urinalysis dipstick test?", "answer": "A rapid test for urine glucose, protein, pH, ketones, and more."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in dipstick test?", "answer": "Enzyme reagents like glucose oxidase, diazonium salts, and indicator dyes."},
{"question": "What is coagulation factor assay?", "answer": "Measures activity of clotting factors in blood."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in factor assay?", "answer": "Specific substrates and reagents for each clotting factor."},
{"question": "What is mycology test?", "answer": "Identifies fungal infections from clinical specimens."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in fungal culture?", "answer": "Sabouraud Dextrose Agar (SDA) and lactophenol cotton blue for staining."},
{"question": "What is parasitology test?", "answer": "Detects parasites in stool, blood, or tissues."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in malaria test?", "answer": "Giemsa stain or rapid diagnostic test reagents."},
{"question": "What is toxicology test?", "answer": "Detects presence of drugs or toxins in biological samples."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in toxicology test?", "answer": "Solvents, reagents, and chromatography materials depending on test."},
{"question": "What is blood gas analysis?", "answer": "Measures oxygen, carbon dioxide, and pH levels in blood."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in blood gas analysis?", "answer": "Electrolyte solutions and electrode buffers in blood gas analyzer."},
{"question": "What is hemoglobin test?", "answer": "Measures hemoglobin concentration in blood to detect anemia or polycythemia."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in hemoglobin test?", "answer": "Cyanmethemoglobin reagent or automated analyzer reagents."},
{"question": "What is sickle cell test?", "answer": "Detects sickle-shaped red blood cells in blood."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in sickle cell test?", "answer": "Sodium metabisulfite in slide sickling test."},
{"question": "What is blood culture?", "answer": "Detects bacteria or fungi in blood samples."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in blood culture?", "answer": "Broth media like BHI or tryptic soy broth and anticoagulants like SPS."},
{"question": "What is Coombs test?", "answer": "Detects antibodies attached to red blood cells for autoimmune hemolysis."},
{"question": "Which chemical is used in Coombs test?", "answer": "Anti-human globulin (Coombs reagent)."},
{"question": "What is radiology?", "answer": "Radiology is the medical specialty that uses imaging techniques to diagnose and treat diseases."},
{"question": "What is X-ray imaging?", "answer": "X-ray imaging uses electromagnetic radiation to visualize bones and certain tissues."},
{"question": "What is CT scan?", "answer": "Computed Tomography (CT) scan produces cross-sectional images of the body using X-rays."},
{"question": "What is MRI?", "answer": "Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) uses magnetic fields and radio waves to produce detailed images of organs and tissues."},
{"question": "What is ultrasound?", "answer": "Ultrasound uses high-frequency sound waves to create images of internal organs."},
{"question": "What is fluoroscopy?", "answer": "Fluoroscopy provides real-time moving images of internal structures using X-rays."},
{"question": "What is PET scan?", "answer": "Positron Emission Tomography (PET) uses radioactive tracers to assess metabolic activity."},
{"question": "What is SPECT scan?", "answer": "Single Photon Emission Computed Tomography (SPECT) uses gamma rays to produce 3D images of organs."},
{"question": "What is mammography?", "answer": "Mammography is X-ray imaging of the breast to detect tumors or abnormalities."},
{"question": "What is barium swallow?", "answer": "Barium swallow is an X-ray test to examine the esophagus using barium contrast."},
{"question": "What is barium enema?", "answer": "Barium enema is an X-ray examination of the colon using barium contrast."},
{"question": "What is contrast media?", "answer": "Contrast media are substances used to improve visibility of structures in imaging studies."},
{"question": "What is iodinated contrast?", "answer": "Iodinated contrast is used in CT scans and angiography to enhance blood vessels and organs."},
{"question": "What is gadolinium?", "answer": "Gadolinium is a contrast agent used in MRI scans."},
{"question": "What is radiograph?", "answer": "A radiograph is an image produced by X-ray imaging."},
{"question": "What is digital radiography?", "answer": "Digital radiography uses digital detectors instead of film to capture X-ray images."},
{"question": "What is interventional radiology?", "answer": "Interventional radiology uses imaging guidance to perform minimally invasive procedures."},
{"question": "What is angiography?", "answer": "Angiography visualizes blood vessels using contrast media and X-rays."},
{"question": "What is CT angiography?", "answer": "CT angiography combines CT imaging with contrast injection to visualize blood vessels."},
{"question": "What is MRI angiography?", "answer": "MRI angiography uses magnetic resonance to visualize blood vessels without radiation."},
{"question": "What is DEXA scan?", "answer": "DEXA scan measures bone mineral density to diagnose osteoporosis."},
{"question": "What is nuclear medicine?", "answer": "Nuclear medicine uses small amounts of radioactive substances to diagnose or treat disease."},
{"question": "What is radionuclide scan?", "answer": "A scan using radioactive tracers to evaluate organ function or detect disease."},
{"question": "What is CT colonography?", "answer": "CT colonography is a virtual colonoscopy using CT imaging to detect polyps or cancer."},
{"question": "What is chest X-ray?", "answer": "Chest X-ray images the lungs, heart, and chest wall."},
{"question": "What is abdominal X-ray?", "answer": "Abdominal X-ray evaluates abdominal organs, bowel gas, or obstruction."},
{"question": "What is head CT?", "answer": "CT scan of the head is used to detect trauma, stroke, or brain tumors."},
{"question": "What is brain MRI?", "answer": "MRI of the brain provides detailed images for stroke, tumors, or neurological conditions."},
{"question": "What is echocardiography?", "answer": "Echocardiography uses ultrasound to visualize heart structure and function."},
{"question": "What is Doppler ultrasound?", "answer": "Doppler ultrasound measures blood flow and velocity in vessels."},
{"question": "What is interventional CT?", "answer": "CT-guided procedures such as biopsies or drain placements."},
{"question": "What is interventional MRI?", "answer": "MRI-guided minimally invasive procedures like biopsies."},
{"question": "What is radiographic contrast?", "answer": "Contrast used to improve visibility of tissues in X-rays or CT scans."},
{"question": "What is intravenous contrast?", "answer": "Contrast injected into veins to highlight blood vessels or organs during imaging."},
{"question": "What is oral contrast?", "answer": "Contrast taken by mouth to visualize the gastrointestinal tract in imaging studies."},
{"question": "What is radiofrequency ablation?", "answer": "A minimally invasive treatment using imaging guidance and heat to destroy abnormal tissue."},
{"question": "What is mammogram screening?", "answer": "Routine X-ray of breasts to detect early-stage breast cancer."},
{"question": "What is portable X-ray?", "answer": "X-ray machine that can be moved to the patient bedside for imaging."},
{"question": "What is C-arm?", "answer": "A mobile fluoroscopy device used during surgical procedures."},
{"question": "What is PACS?", "answer": "Picture Archiving and Communication System stores and shares digital medical images."},
{"question": "What is teleradiology?", "answer": "Transmission of radiologic images for remote interpretation."},
{"question": "What is nuclear scan for thyroid?", "answer": "Uses radioactive iodine or technetium to assess thyroid function or nodules."},
{"question": "What is bone scan?", "answer": "A nuclear medicine test that detects bone abnormalities using radioactive tracers."},
{"question": "What is gallium scan?", "answer": "Nuclear medicine scan to detect infections, inflammation, or tumors."},
{"question": "What is ventilation-perfusion (V/Q) scan?", "answer": "Evaluates lung ventilation and blood flow using radioactive tracers."},
{"question": "What is PET-CT?", "answer": "Combination of PET and CT for both functional and anatomical imaging."},
{"question": "What is functional MRI (fMRI)?", "answer": "fMRI measures brain activity by detecting changes in blood flow."},
{"question": "What is diffusion MRI?", "answer": "MRI technique that evaluates water diffusion in tissues, useful for stroke detection."},
{"question": "What is mammary ultrasonography?", "answer": "Ultrasound imaging of breast tissue to detect lumps or cysts."},
{"question": "What is contrast-enhanced CT?", "answer": "CT scan performed after injecting contrast to improve tissue differentiation."},
{"question": "What is contrast-enhanced MRI?", "answer": "MRI performed after gadolinium injection to highlight structures."},
{"question": "What is interventional angiography?", "answer": "Procedures like stent placement or embolization using imaging guidance."},
{"question": "What is pediatric radiology?", "answer": "Radiology specialization for imaging infants and children."},
{"question": "What is fetal ultrasound?", "answer": "Ultrasound imaging of a fetus to monitor growth and detect anomalies."},
{"question": "What is digital subtraction angiography?", "answer": "Technique to visualize blood vessels by subtracting pre-contrast images from post-contrast images."},
{"question": "What is mammography compression?", "answer": "Compression of breast tissue to reduce radiation dose and improve image quality."},
{"question": "What is imaging modality?", "answer": "A type of imaging technology like X-ray, CT, MRI, ultrasound, or PET."},
{"question": "What is radiation dose?", "answer": "Amount of ionizing radiation received by patient during imaging."},
{"question": "What is CT slice thickness?", "answer": "The thickness of each image slice in CT scan, affecting resolution."},
{"question": "What is MRI sequence?", "answer": "Specific MRI scanning protocol (T1, T2, FLAIR) for tissue visualization."},
{"question": "What is gradient echo MRI?", "answer": "MRI technique using gradient pulses for fast imaging or vascular studies."},
{"question": "What is CT angiography protocol?", "answer": "Injection of iodinated contrast with timed scanning to visualize vessels."},
{"question": "What is MRI safety?", "answer": "Precautions to avoid ferromagnetic objects, implants, and contrast reactions."},
{"question": "What is lead shielding?", "answer": "Use of lead aprons or barriers to protect patients from radiation exposure."},
{"question": "What is radiopharmaceutical?", "answer": "Radioactive compound used in nuclear medicine imaging or therapy."},
{"question": "What is CT perfusion?", "answer": "CT imaging to assess blood flow to tissues like brain or heart."},
{"question": "What is MR spectroscopy?", "answer": "MRI technique to evaluate chemical composition of tissues."},
{"question": "What is dual-energy CT?", "answer": "CT imaging using two different X-ray energy levels to improve tissue contrast."},
{"question": "What is low-dose CT?", "answer": "CT scan using reduced radiation dose, often for screening like lung cancer."},
{"question": "What is high-resolution CT?", "answer": "CT scan with thin slices for detailed imaging of lungs or small structures."},
{"question": "What is CT-guided biopsy?", "answer": "Biopsy performed under CT imaging to accurately target lesions."},
{"question": "What is MRI-guided biopsy?", "answer": "Biopsy performed under MRI guidance for precise tissue sampling."},
{"question": "What is portable ultrasound?", "answer": "Compact ultrasound device used at bedside or in emergency settings."},
{"question": "What is 3D reconstruction in imaging?", "answer": "Technique to create 3D images from CT or MRI slices for better visualization."},
{"question": "What is radionuclide therapy?", "answer": "Treatment using radioactive substances to target cancer cells."},
{"question": "What is cardiac CT?", "answer": "CT scan to visualize coronary arteries and heart anatomy."},
{"question": "What is MRI of spine?", "answer": "MRI imaging to evaluate vertebrae, discs, spinal cord, and nerves."},
{"question": "What is thoracic imaging?", "answer": "Imaging of chest organs including lungs, heart, and mediastinum."},
{"question": "What is abdominal imaging?", "answer": "Imaging of abdomen and pelvis to evaluate organs and detect pathology."},
{"question": "What is head and neck imaging?", "answer": "CT or MRI to assess brain, skull, sinuses, and soft tissues of head and neck."},
{"question": "What is musculoskeletal imaging?", "answer": "Imaging of bones, joints, muscles, and soft tissues for injury or disease."},
{"question": "What is trauma radiology?", "answer": "Radiology focused on imaging patients with traumatic injuries."},
{"question": "What is contrast reaction?", "answer": "Allergic or adverse reaction to contrast media during imaging studies."},
{"question": "What is sedation in radiology?", "answer": "Use of medications to relax or sedate patients during imaging procedures."},
{"question": "What is MRI coil?", "answer": "Device used to detect MRI signals from specific body parts."},
{"question": "What is image post-processing?", "answer": "Techniques applied to medical images to enhance or analyze them."},
{"question": "What is cine imaging?", "answer": "Imaging technique to capture moving organs, often in cardiac MRI or fluoroscopy."},
{"question": "What is functional imaging?", "answer": "Imaging assessing physiological processes like blood flow or metabolism."},
{"question": "What is contrast extravasation?", "answer": "Leakage of contrast agent outside the vessel during imaging."},
{"question": "What is radiation therapy planning?", "answer": "Use of imaging to guide precise delivery of radiation treatment."},
{"question": "What is interventional oncology?", "answer": "Minimally invasive cancer treatment guided by imaging techniques."},
{"question": "What is DICOM?", "answer": "Digital Imaging and Communications in Medicine, a standard for storing and sharing medical images."},
